<br>
I have some magic items equipped, but nothing too special. I would really like to quest for some nice equipment to boost my essential stats. I've heard of the Stein of Moggok. Is that something that can be done at my level. Is it worth it? Also, is the Staff of Observers something that is worth questing for?<br>
<br>
I've been playing for a long time. I always solo, which explains why I am only lvl 24 even though I have been playing for around 2 years! I also got Kunark just recently, so I am just now reaping the rewards of exp and loot at Lake of Ill Omen. <br>
<br>
Anyway, sometimes I get real bored with just trying to level. I would really like to do some worthwhile quests. You know, I wanna feel like there is a purpose  to my existance! Actually, I just really want to get some cool stuff. <br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for your suggestions. <br>
<br>
Minlo  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usehra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sehra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 434<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/02 5:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=913.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Quest advice for a lvl 24 Mage?</span><hr size=1> At level 24, make sure you have your waterpet. I believe it is research only. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Check out Gargoyles in OOT. They drop eyes for the shovel, and any spares you get sell for around 9 plat each.<br>
<br>
This is assuming that those are still there. I heard VI was changing it, but that may only be on Legends...<br>
<br>
Also, for GREAT xp at that level, look into the 2 and 3 spawn brute caves near the zone to Dalnirs in Warslick's Woods.<br>
<br>
