<br>
Most of the items are easy to get by 24. What you can't loot, you can usually buy for not much plat.  The hardest part is the toes. Check in OOT to see if anyone is camping Gornit, or in the zones where the giants live. You can also find toes at vendors thoughout Norath.<br>
<br>
The other hard part was the gems. I found it difficult to pay about 100pp for a gem, while trying to buy my spells. But with persistence it can be done. And its worth it. The difference these items make in your pets starts to become more noticeable at 24.<br>
<br>
Kaslin Fyrestar<br>
32 Mage in Amazon Storm<br>
Seventh Hammer<br>
<br>
&quot;Has anyone seen my pet?  Hey... where did everyone go?&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uizarek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izarek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#333333>(3/18/02 3:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=913.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Quest advice for a lvl 24 Mage?</span><hr size=1> The main items for the focus quests are off some of the crocs outside of Cazic-Thule or Magician's in Najena.  You also get torn pages which you can save for you epic.  You'll probably need a group for either at 24.<br>
<br>
I got the toes from vendors in Freeport near the docks or hanging out asking people camping gornit for toes.<br>
<br>
I bought the griffon feather, the gargoyle eye off vendors.  Just random vendors where people have sold them.  The two scales I hunted for.  I think both creatures (fire drake in Lavastorm, siren in OOT) are both doable at 24.<br>
<br>
I would wait until level 34 (when the focus items start making a big difference).  Although I did them at 29.  Got enough money hunting to buy the gems.  Between that an research blew out my bank account.<br>
<br>
But basically check out all the mage quests in Temple of Solusek Ro.  The robe, circlet of mist, earthen boots and clay bracelet are all interesting quests to do, but often require a group to do.  I did the boots and bracelet solo at 54.  I didn't bother with the circlet or robe since I had better by then.<br>
<br>
If you are don't care about doing quests, just do the boots and focus items.  Then find the best place to farm plat and buy what you want.  Gargoyles in OOT or wisps on Erud's crossing isn't so bad.  Just make sure you do the GLS quest and not sell them to vendors.<br>
<br>
In general most quests are very hard to do solo at a level where the quest is worth it.  So unless you have a good group of friends who want to go interesting places (like Mistmoore, Upper Guk, Najena, Unrest) there aren't many decent quests to do at 24.  The other alternative is to hang out in those places and ask people to loot what to them are useless quest items.<br>
<br>
Izarek<br>
